validates_area_code
===================
This plugin extends ActiveRecord::Validations to include a telephone area code validation.
It uses the data provided by the North American Numbering Plan Administration (NANPA) for its validation.

Additional Options
==================
The additional options and arguments (:if, :message) are the same provided by the default ActiveRecord's validations.

Current Release
===============
Version: 0.1
Date: 10/23/2007

Example
=======
class User < ActiveRecord::Base
  validates_area_code :phone, :allow_toll_free => false, :format => {:with => /\d{3}-\d{3}-\d{4}/, :message => 'is invalid. Should be XXX-XXX-XXXX'}
end

